sql:
SELECT hiring_managers.name, messages.channel
FROM hiring_managers
INNER JOIN messages ON hiring_managers.email = messages.sender;

external_knowledge:
- "beacons of opportunity" refers to job postings;
- "shone brightly" implies that the job postings have been highly rated;
- "perfect interview glow" means the interviews were rated 5;
- "welcomed into the fold" represents the job offers being accepted;
- "confirmed handshake" metaphorically indicates a confirmed job offer status.

- "Shone brightly in their interviews" refers to candidates with ratings higher than 4;
- "Actively applied for roles" means the candidates have entries in the job applications table;
- "Still on the radar for scheduling meetings" indicates that the candidates have entries in the calendars table, suggesting their availability for further interactions;
- The metaphor of "stars that stand out in the night sky" refers to candidates who are notably successful based on their interview performance and active engagement in the hiring process.

